======== Building a new installation *.exe file ========

This only works if you setup the Developer version of LaueG

In the "My Stuff" menu of LaueG run:
	"Save Source"
	"Create Release Code"
	"Generate Build Folder"

Go to C:\DevApps\LaueG\_Release\ and run WindowsInstall.iss which will start Inno Setup

Within Inno Setup, run Compile from the Build menu

The setup file LaueG_setup_<date>.exe will be created in C:\DevApps\LaueG\_Release\Installs\

As a bonus, all source files are copied to C:\DevApps\LaueG\_Release\Source\
